{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "66bcbe01ae81d148616b15d3", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 3, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 150, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "MOG", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9a"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "64b850022a7d64ecd80b00a6", "title": "NEET 2007", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "Three point charges $+q,-2 q$ are placed at points $(x=0, y=a, z=0),(x=0, y=0, z$ $=0)$ and $(x=a, y=0, z=0)$ respectively. The magnitude and direction of the electric dipole moment vector of this charge assembly are:", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "9mc1S", "text": "$\\sqrt{2} q a$ along the line joining points $(x=0, y=0, z=0)$ and $(x=a, y=a$, $z=0)$", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "S6c4m", "text": "$q a$ along the line joining points $(x=0$, $y=0, z=0)$ and $(x=a, y=a, z=0)$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "lFBcI", "text": "$\\sqrt{2} q a$ along $+x$ direction", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "Za2fO", "text": "$\\sqrt{2} q a$ along $+y$ direction", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "This consists of two dipoles, $-q$ and $+q$ with dipole moment along with the $+y$ direction and $-q$ and $+q$ along the X-direction\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/neet/59-J0aOMXhS7MjGRpPlgBTSbY9jYAG6p_Xefxw0g6xY.original.fullsize.png\"><br>$\\therefore$ The resultant moment\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& =\\sqrt{q^2 a^2+q^2 a^2} \\\\\n& =\\sqrt{2} q a\n\\end{aligned}$\nAlong the direction $45^{\\circ}$ that is along OP where $\\mathrm{P}$ is $(+a, a, 0)$", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MO